918{

925}

979static inline bool setJSSVGElement_styleSetter(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, JSSVGElement& thisObject, JSValue value)
980{
981 auto& vm = JSC::getVM(&lexicalGlobalObject);
982 auto throwScope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
983 auto id = Identifier::fromString(vm, reinterpret_cast<const LChar*>("style"), strlen("style"));
984 auto valueToForwardTo = thisObject.get(&lexicalGlobalObject, id);
985 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(throwScope, false);
986 if (UNLIKELY(!valueToForwardTo.isObject())) {
987 throwTypeError(&lexicalGlobalObject, throwScope);
988 return false;
989 }
990 auto forwardId = Identifier::fromString(vm, reinterpret_cast<const LChar*>("cssText"), strlen("cssText"));
991 PutPropertySlot slot(valueToForwardTo, false);
992 asObject(valueToForwardTo)->methodTable(vm)->put(asObject(valueToForwardTo), &lexicalGlobalObject, forwardId, value, slot);
993 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(throwScope, false);
994 return true;
995}

998{
999 return IDLAttribute<JSSVGElement>::set<setJSSVGElement_styleSetter>(*lexicalGlobalObject, thisValue, encodedValue, attributeName);
1000}

1002#if ENABLE(CSS_TYPED_OM)
1003static inline JSValue jsSVGElement_attributeStyleMapGetter(JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, JSSVGElement& thisObject)
1004{
1005 auto& vm = JSC::getVM(&lexicalGlobalObject);
1006 auto throwScope = DECLARE_THROW_SCOPE(vm);
1007 if (JSValue cachedValue = thisObject.m_attributeStyleMap.get())
1008 return cachedValue;
1009 auto& impl = thisObject.wrapped();
1010 JSValue result = toJS<IDLInterface<StylePropertyMap>>(lexicalGlobalObject, *thisObject.globalObject(), throwScope, impl.ensureAttributeStyleMap());
1011 RETURN_IF_EXCEPTION(throwScope, { });
1012 thisObject.m_attributeStyleMap.set(JSC::getVM(&lexicalGlobalObject), &thisObject, result);
1013 return result;
1014}

3754
3755JSC::IsoSubspace* JSSVGElement::subspaceForImpl(JSC::VM& vm)
3756{
3757 auto& clientData = *static_cast<JSVMClientData*>(vm.clientData);
3758 auto& spaces = clientData.subspaces();
3759 if (auto* space = spaces.m_subspaceForSVGElement.get())
3760 return space;
3761 static_assert(std::is_base_of_v<JSC::JSDestructibleObject, JSSVGElement> || !JSSVGElement::needsDestruction);
3762 if constexpr (std::is_base_of_v<JSC::JSDestructibleObject, JSSVGElement>)
3763 spaces.m_subspaceForSVGElement = makeUnique<IsoSubspace> ISO_SUBSPACE_INIT(vm.heap, vm.destructibleObjectHeapCellType.get(), JSSVGElement);
3764 else
3765 spaces.m_subspaceForSVGElement = makeUnique<IsoSubspace> ISO_SUBSPACE_INIT(vm.heap, vm.cellHeapCellType.get(), JSSVGElement);
3766 auto* space = spaces.m_subspaceForSVGElement.get();
3767IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("unreachable-code")
3768IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("tautological-compare")
3769 void (*myVisitOutputConstraint)(JSC::JSCell*, JSC::SlotVisitor&) = JSSVGElement::visitOutputConstraints;
3770 void (*jsCellVisitOutputConstraint)(JSC::JSCell*, JSC::SlotVisitor&) = JSC::JSCell::visitOutputConstraints;
3771 if (myVisitOutputConstraint != jsCellVisitOutputConstraint)
3772 clientData.outputConstraintSpaces().append(space);
3773IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
3774IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
3775 return space;
3776}
